



Head Quarters, Cambridge, Jany 19th 1776



Parole New-Haven.
Countersign Lee.


One serjeant, one Corporal and twelve Men, from General Putnams division, to mount to morrow Morning for the Provost Guard, at the old School house, on Cambridge common; to this Guard all Prisoners accused of Crimes cognizable by a General Court Martial, are to be sent; all suspected spies, and all Strollers and Stragglers, who cannot give a proper account of themselvesThe Guard is to be under the immediate command of the Provost, and he is only to receive Orders from Head Quarters,
[145]
the General in Chief, the Adjutant and Quarter Master Generals for the time being.
